   "source": [
    "# Fit de franges d’interférence"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cfd3abf1",
   "metadata": {
    "mystnb": {
     "image": {
      "width": "200px"
     }
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "On souhaite ajuster les franges d’un interféromètre atomique. Les données sont dans le fichier {download}`data/fit_sinus.dat <data/fit_sinus.dat>`. La première colonne du fichiers (axe x) représente une fréquence en Hz. La seconde colonne représente la population mesurée pour une fréquence donnée. L’objectif est de trouver la position de la frange centrale.\n",
    "\n",
    "Voici à quoi ressemblent les données : \n",
    "\n",
    "```{image} data_interfero.png\n",
    ":alt: Interferometre atomique\n",
    ":width: 70%\n",
    ":align: center\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "On ajustera par une fonction cosinus avec une amplitude, une moyenne, une position de la frange centrale et une largeur ajustable (interfrange), soit en tout quatre paramètres.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Lire le fichier et tracer les données.\n",
    "\n",
    "2. Écrire  la   fonction   de   fit   qui   dépend   des   paramètres   ci   dessus.   On   appellera frange(x, ...).  Tracez  la  courbe  pour  x  entre ±220 Hz avec des paramètres raisonables.  On  prendra  un  inter-frange de 200 Hz.\n",
    "\n",
    "3. Calculer les paramètres optimaux. Quelle est la position la frange centrale ? Représentez les points et la courbe.\n",
    "\n",
    "4. Quelle est l’incertitude sur la position de la frange centrale ?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "501f2f54",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "sol"
    ]
   },
   "source": [
    "--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
    "\n",
    "## Solution"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "76a47f59",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from scipy.optimize import curve_fit\n",
    "import numpy as np"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "be722b88",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "Text(0, 0.5, 'Amplitude')"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 2,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "freq, amp = np.loadtxt('data/fit_sinus.dat', unpack=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig = plt.figure()\n",
    "ax = fig.subplots(1, 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.plot(freq, amp, 'o')\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Fréquence (Hz)')\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Amplitude')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "a2c66d7b",
   "metadata": {
    "scrolled": true
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "Text(0.5, 0, 'Fréquence (Hz)')"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 3,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "def frange(x, a, b, f_0, Delta_f):\n",
    "    return a + b*np.cos(2*np.pi*(x-f_0)/Delta_f)\n",
    "\n",
    "p0 = (0.2, 0.1, 0, 200)\n",
    "\n",
    "f_plot = np.linspace(-220, 220)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig = plt.figure()\n",
    "ax = fig.subplots(1, 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.plot(freq, amp, 'o')\n",
    "ax.plot(f_plot, frange(f_plot, *p0))\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Fréquence (Hz)')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "e60571c8",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "Text(0.5, 0, 'Fréquence (Hz)')"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 4,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "p_opt, p_cov = curve_fit(frange, freq, amp, p0=p0)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig = plt.figure()\n",
    "ax = fig.subplots(1, 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.plot(freq, amp, 'o')\n",
    "ax.plot(f_plot, frange(f_plot, *p_opt))\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Fréquence (Hz)')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "2b1e884a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Position de la frange :2.37\n",
      "Incertitude de la frange :0.32\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "a, b, f_0, Delta_f = p_opt\n",
    "incertitude = np.sqrt(p_cov[2, 2])\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Position de la frange :{f_0:.2f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Incertitude de la frange :{incertitude:.2f}\")"
   ]
  },
